This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with skin lesion segmentation on dermoscopic images using deep learning methods. It also involves regularization and self-ensembling techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves the use of deep learning models and optimization techniques. 

Multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories are also possible as the paper deals with image analysis and segmentation, which are important components of multimedia and information retrieval systems.
